# build-typography-architecture (Hexa Design System)

Takes typography variables in the **Hexa Design System** file — wherever they currently live,
however they're typed — and folds them into Hexa's established 3-tier architecture:
**Font-Family** and **Font-Weight** primitives live under `1. Primitives`, font **sizes** resolve
through Hexa's existing `Scale` ramp (also under `1. Primitives`, never duplicated), and the full
typography token set (Title/Screen, Title/Section, Title/Subsection, Title/Body, Body, Caption,
Display) lives under `2. Tokens > Typography`, aliasing Tier 1 only, with identical values across
Hexa's 5 brand modes unless explicitly told otherwise. Any legacy ad-hoc collection (e.g. a
standalone `Typography` / `Typography Primitives` pair) is deleted once migration is verified.

This is the Hexa-specific version of this workflow — it hardcodes Hexa's known structure rather
than rediscovering it each run. When this gets generalized into a reusable template under
`ds-claude-context`, the hardcoded facts below (collection names, Scale formula, mode list)
become the parts that get re-derived per project.

---

## Hexa's known architecture (treat as ground truth, not something to re-derive)

| Fact | Value |
|---|---|
| File | Hexa Design System (`xVyGzJn1YYJbDoQwVOfFho`) |
| Tier 1 collection | `1. Primitives` — single mode (`Default`) |
| Tier 2 collection | `2. Tokens` — 5 modes: `Default`, `Lite`, `Priority`, `Privilege`, `Wealth` |
| Tier 3 collection | `3. Semantics` — same 5 modes as Tier 2 |
| Scale naming formula | `name = value × 25` (e.g. `Scale/600` = `24`) — two fixed exceptions: `Scale/1000` = `1000`, `Scale/1` = `1` |
| Typography Tier 1 groups | `Typography/Font-Family/[Step]`, `Typography/Font-Weight/[Step]` — both `STRING` |
| Typography Tier 2 location | `2. Tokens > Typography/...` — never a standalone collection |
| Font Family value | `Poppins`, primitive name `Typography/Font-Family/Sans-Serif` |
| Font Weight values | `Typography/Font-Weight/Regular` = `"400"`, `Typography/Font-Weight/Medium` = `"500"`, `Typography/Font-Weight/Medium Underline` = `"Medium Underline"` (decoration value, not a true weight — kept here as an explicit placeholder pending a future Text-Decoration tier) |

If a future session finds any of these facts have changed (e.g. a 6th brand mode added, or the
Scale formula no longer holds for new steps), stop and surface the discrepancy before proceeding —
don't silently follow this table over live file state.

