## Standing naming & structure conventions

- **Tier 1 location**: `1. Primitives > Typography/Font-Family/[Step]` and
  `1. Primitives > Typography/Font-Weight/[Step]` — sibling groups to `Color/` and `Scale/` in the
  same collection, never a separate collection.
- **Sizes are not a Typography primitive.** Font sizes resolve through `1. Primitives > Scale`,
  not a `Typography/Font-Size/` group. Add missing `Scale` steps first (Phase 2a) using
  `name = value × 25` if a new type style needs a size that doesn't exist yet.
- **Tier 2 location**: `2. Tokens > Typography/...`, aliasing Tier 1 only — never its own
  collection, since it must ride Hexa's existing 5-mode brand structure.
- **Type fidelity over convenience**: sizes are real `FLOAT` variables aliasing `Scale`. Family
  and weight are `STRING` (categorical/text values, not magnitudes).
- **Anomalous values get a parking spot, not a force-fit.** A value that doesn't match its
  apparent category (the precedent: `Weight Medium Underline`, a decoration value, not a numeric
  weight) gets its own clearly-named placeholder under the closest existing group rather than
  being dropped into `Font-Weight` proper or invented a whole new tier without sign-off.
- **5-mode default**: unless told otherwise, new Tier 2 typography values are identical across
  `Default`, `Lite`, `Priority`, `Privilege`, `Wealth`. Per-brand typography differences are a
  deliberate, explicitly-requested exception, not a default.

