## Phases at a glance

```
Phase 0 — Discovery                          (read-only)
    └── Inventory the typography variable(s) relevant to this run (new style? stray collection?
         existing token to audit?) — values, types, current location
    └── Cross-reference any size values against 1. Primitives > Scale by VALUE, not name/assumption
         ↓
Phase 1 — Surface findings                   (read-only)
    └── Report exact overlap/gap vs. Scale; flag any anomalous or stray values found
         ↓
    ⛔ HUMAN GATE A — confirm gap list and anomaly handling
         ↓
Phase 2 — Tier 1 build
    └── 2a. Fill any Scale gaps using name = value × 25
    └── 2b. Create/extend Typography/Font-Family or Typography/Font-Weight in 1. Primitives,
         in a sensible logical order (no reorder API — get order right at creation)
         ↓
    ⛔ HUMAN GATE B — confirm naming and resolvedType choices
         ↓
Phase 3 — Tier 2 build
    └── Recreate/extend the relevant token variable(s) under 2. Tokens > Typography — sizes as
         FLOAT aliasing Scale, family/weight as STRING aliasing Tier 1, identical across all 5
         brand modes unless told otherwise
    └── KEY GOTCHA: Figma cannot alias across resolvedType (STRING ↔ FLOAT). A STRING-typed
         legacy size variable must be deleted and recreated as FLOAT — there is no in-place type
         change. Recreating breaks existing node bindings to the old ID.
         ↓
    ⛔ HUMAN GATE C — sign off on any recreate-vs-keep decision for type-mismatched variables
         before writing anything
         ↓
Phase 4 — Bind deferred/anomalous values
    └── Once the user has said where a parked value belongs, create its real Tier 1 home and
         re-point the Tier 2 variable(s) to it
         ↓
Phase 5 — Verify before cleanup
    └── Re-fetch 2. Tokens > Typography with resolveAliases — confirm every value/type matches
         expectations across all 5 modes
         ↓
    ⛔ HUMAN GATE D — confirm verification is clean, and confirm whether live nodes/components are
         bound to anything about to be deleted
         ↓
Phase 6 — Cleanup (only if this run involves removing a legacy/stray collection)
    └── Delete any collection sitting outside 1. Primitives / 2. Tokens / 3. Semantics
         ↓
Phase 7 — Final verify
    └── Re-fetch full file variable summary — assert only the 3 tier collections remain
```

